      <p class="scale-strip">
        For comparison, your simulated beach swings about <strong>20 pixels</strong> top to bottom — call it
        a humble <strong>3 ft</strong> if each pixel were an inch. Most of us live with tides this size and
        never notice them. Imagine a beach where the parking lot vanishes by lunchtime.
      </p>
