    <!-- Behind the Waves -->
    <section class="mt-10 pt-8" style="border-top: 1px solid rgba(245, 198, 160, 0.1);">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-5" style="color: rgba(245, 198, 160, 0.35); font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;">Behind the Waves</h2>
      <div class="behind-grid">
        <div class="behind-card">
          <p class="behind-card-title">Tide physics</p>
          <p class="behind-card-body">The waterline is calculated per column using three overlapping sine waves — a slow ~15s surge, a medium lateral sweep, and a fast surface ripple. Each column gets a slightly different phase, so the water bends and curves across the beach rather than moving as a flat wall.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="behind-card">
          <p class="behind-card-title">Castle erosion</p>
          <p class="behind-card-body">Each block under the waterline accumulates erosion damage over time. Once a block crumbles, any blocks above it with no lateral support collapse — tall thin towers fall faster than wide bases. Debris becomes particles that drift upward and fade.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="behind-card">
          <p class="behind-card-title">Color &amp; themes</p>
          <p class="behind-card-body">Each theme defines five color palettes: dry sand, wet sand, shallow water, deep water, and castle stone. A slow hue-shift cycle (±10°) animates the water over time without touching the sand — the ocean feels alive while the beach stays still.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="behind-card">
          <p class="behind-card-title">Seagulls</p>
          <p class="behind-card-body">Four seagulls wander the canvas. Each tracks the tide line in its column and lerps its position to stay above the water. They switch between a flying W-shape silhouette and a walking stance with alternating feet depending on whether they're moving or standing still.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <script>
    const validThemes = ['tropical', 'sunset', 'arctic', 'night'];
    const params = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);
    const requested = params.get('theme');
    const active = validThemes.includes(requested ?? '') ? requested : 'tropical';
    const card = document.querySelector(`.beach-card[data-theme="${active}"]`);
    if (card) {
      card.classList.add('is-active');
      const label = card.querySelector('[data-active-label]');
      if (label) label.removeAttribute('hidden');
    }
  </script>
